"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, I did a video not so long ago talking about how much I appreciate people who come and help. Volunteers, and a good friend of mine, Rachel has been by several times to volunteer. I met a good friend of mine, Pete, who uh I'm gonna probably recruit to try to help me volunteer and some other close friends who are very interested in the idea, haven't just had a chance to come by yet, and that's partially on me as well. And also I met someone at the farmers market, Megan. Uh, I've already lost your number. And she was looking to help me volunteer. Um, met her at the farmers market, she follows my videos. And so please comment if you see the say I need your phone number again or text me again. Anyway, um, one of the things about my garden is that I'm not always very organized. I'm not a very good gardener yet. I'm real good with the soil, but my gardening needs some help. And so I'm trying to get more organized and I'm trying to set it up so that I can take volunteer help more easily so that I, you know, create a list of things that I can always be doing, and that's one of the things I'm working on now, is just trying to come up with better ways to get help. Anyway, um, if you know anybody who wants to come and help, or more importantly, if you know somebody who wants to kind of join in this, um, I will drop off vegetable refugees so that you can compost yourself, and then I will turn you on to the markets to sell them. Um, if you know a person who would be interested in this, or if you're interested in this yourself, give me a comment. I'm in Houston, Texas, and I need help. I need help with uh garden space, I need help with composting, I need help with my own garden. I'd like to recruit people who have their own gardens or their own growing spaces to come join me. Um, just give me a comment. Thanks, y'all. Appreciate it.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, I did a video not so long ago talking about how much 